– 2 –
19 retail seller, as defined in section 1.3 of this bill. Under section 3.3, a remote retail
20 seller is subject to this tax only if the remote retail seller meets certain thresholds
21 for the retail sale of cigars or pipe tobacco to consumers in this State. Section 3.4 of
22 this bill provides for the filing of a monthly report of the sales of cigars and pipe
23 tobacco by a remote retail seller in a manner similar to the monthly report for a
24 wholesale dealer of such products, and section 3.5 of this bill imposes
25 recordkeeping requirements on a remote retail seller of cigars and pipe tobacco that
26 are similar to the recordkeeping requirements for a wholesale dealer of such
27 products. Sections 3.6-3.9 of this bill provide for the licensing of remote retail
28 sellers of cigars and pipe tobacco in the same manner as wholesale dealers of such
29 products. Specifically: (1) section 3.65 prohibits the issuance, maintenance or
30 renewal of a license if the applicant or licensee is not registered to collect and remit
31 sales and use tax, is delinquent in the payment of sales and use tax or the tax
32 imposed by section 3.3, or does not comply with certain age-verification
33 requirements; (2) section 3.8 imposes the same fees for a license that are imposed
34 on similar tobacco licensees; and (3) section 3.9 imposes the same bonding
35 requirements that are imposed on similar tobacco licensees. Section 7 of this bill
36 clarifies requirements for wholesale dealers of tobacco products, other than
37 cigarettes, to maintain an inventory of such products by providing that such
38 inventory must be maintained at each location in this State at which the wholesaler
39 maintains a place of business. Section 12.5 of this bill makes a remote retail seller
40 subject to the penalties that apply under existing law to delinquency in the payment
41 of taxes on tobacco products. (NRS 370.523) Section 20 of this bill makes a
42 conforming change to align with existing requirements for the use of an
43 independent, third-party age verification service by remote retail sellers of certain
44 tobacco products. Section 20.5 of this bill makes a conforming change to ensure
45 premium cigars sold to a remote retail seller are taxed in the same manner as
46 premium cigars sold by other retail sellers in this State. Section 20.7 of this bill
47 makes an appropriation to the Department of Taxation for certain costs to
48 implement the provisions of this bill.
